    "body": "@chriseth Not closed - rather postponed for reconsideration in ``0.5.3`` (resp. put in the backlog - actually I'm moving it now).\r\nThe idea is that the neither the new PPA builds (nor any other release build I think) so far still *don't* link to shared boost, but still have the default static linking enabled. However, that's actually bad style for the PPAs, so I'd suggest to change that and then we should have a test run for it. But we said we wanted to have small incremental changes and don't want to change everything at once, so: postponed.",
